---
alwaysApply: true
---

Code consistency and clean development
- Follow existing patterns and naming conventions in the codebase.
- Avoid duplication; reuse existing logic.
- Do not introduce unnecessary abstractions.
- Prefer clear, readable code over clever solutions.

Security-first engineering
- Never expose secrets or credentials; flag potential security or compliance risks.
- Prefer safe defaults over shortcuts.

Stepwise execution and context awareness
- Summarize understanding before implementing.
- Complete one step fully before moving to the next.
- Do not skip steps or jump ahead without confirmation.

Systematic debugging and testing
- Do not guess fixes; explain root cause briefly before proposing a fix.
- Prefer small, verifiable changes.

MVP-first, future-aware
- Focus on MVP delivery; avoid premature optimization.
- Keep future scalability in mind without implementing it early.
- Clearly label suggestions as MVP or post-MVP.
